	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />All I am missing is a good connection to the expansion port.
<br />
<br />If that won't work, I'm working on a backup design that will connect via the second controller port, but that will limit throughput considerably and requires that I can find a good source of male controller connectors.  I don't want to be cutting them off of old NES controllers.
<br />
<br />I've even considered getting an injection molding machine to make my own male controller connectors, but that road sounds like more work than it's worth.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


