		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Sorry tepples, I'm going to have to keep the games as vaporware for now because they rely on a working network adapter.  The plan is to finish up the EtherNES adapter (as other people have dubbed it when dreaming about one in the past) and either offer up kits or completed units with an SDK.  The first titles released that use the SDK will be my own.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":-)" title="Smile" />
<br />
<br />If you want more information on my design for the network adapters, I just wrote a small essay on it in this <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=2901" class="postlink">thread</a>
<br />
<br />PLEASE!  Help me find a part for interfacing with the expansion port.  I have dreamed about having a NES ethernet adapter since 1998 and I now have a good (and CHEAP) design for one that is only missing the expansion port connector.  The whole thing even fits under the snap-in expansion port cover!

		

		</td>
